description.originalText: Gretchen did overnights with us until the baby slept through the night. She truly is the best! She is energetic, yet gentle and our 8 month old absolutelyÂ adored her! Every morning we woke up to the most joyful baby playing and laughing. She is very caring, tidy and dependable. We would love to work with Gretchen again!

Gretchen started with us overnight when our daughter was 5 days old. She is so calm and patient; I felt comfortable leaving my newborn in her care so I could get some sleep. I always woke up refreshed, with the laundry folded and all bottles washed. When she moved to daytime with us, she kept the baby engaged by singing, playing, tummy time and so much more. She was also great with my toddler! It can be hard leaving your baby with someone but I would hands down recommend Gretchen.

description.displayText: Gretchen supported our family for about three years and she was such a great addition to our child-rearing team. She began working with our son as our "Friday nanny" when he was just 7 or 8 months old and stuck with us until after he turned three. She made a seamless transition to supporting both him and our new baby boy for his first year as well. Our boys absolutely loved Gretchen. She brought so much joy and positive energy to the household. She's very playful, creative, engaging, and did a great job getting the boys outside, in the libraries, parks, and science center and so much more. She also did a great job helping socialize him with nanny friends and other neighborhood kids. We couldn't have been happier and feel very fortunate to have had Gretchen in our lives. I asked that she read and engage with our first son in Spanish and she was really diligent about it which, also meant a lot.

description.displayText: Gretchen is the most kind, caring and dependable nanny out there. She cared for our daughter with so much love and kindness. She talked to her, sang to her, played with her, and supported her every moment they spent together and she made us and my daughter so happy. She is an incredibly hard worker and went above and beyond to take care of our baby and our home. I loved working with Gretchen and could not recommend her enough.

description.displayText:
Gretchen is the best! She was with our family since my son was 7 weeks through 13 months, and if my son wasn't starting daycare we would want to keep her with us forever. She is kind, loving, energetic, dependable and most importantly my son absolutely loves her. 

She has more energy than I ever will, and makes sure that our son always feels safe and loved. She helped  him establish consistent routines, preps him healthy meals, and keeps him occupied and busy during the day at the playground and with activities and classes. Not only that, she helps keep our home tidy throughout the day and helps with washing bottles, folding laundry, and organizing the nursery. There is nothing better than walking home from a long day at work to a clean home and a happy, smiling baby. 

We're forever grateful for the care, company and love that she has shown. Her next family will be truly lucky to have her!

description.displayText: We adored Gretchen.  She was so caring AND fun with our little girl.  When we would come home from work, our daughter was all laughing and giggles.  Gretchen also taught her manners and routines as well, so overall was a great influence. I would 100% recommend Gretchen!

description.displayText:
How do I even start... Gretchen is everything you need in a nanny. We used Gretchen for 1 year. She was incredible with our baby girl who was 4 months old at the beginning of our partnership. We would still have her today if we hadn't moved out of the area. 
Gretchen is:
Punctual 
Patient 
Loving / Compassionate  
Detail oriented
Flexible 
Genuine 
She would sing, read and connect with her in a way that most nannies don't. It wasn't just a job for Gretchen, she truly loves kids and it shows up in how she interacts with them. Gretchen knew how to play with her and teach her while also being able to console and comfort her when she needed it. We Love and miss you Gretchen!
